<paragraph id="8BCD94236F04FFE90BFCFD68FE9FFD3E" blockId="122.[189,303,680,706]" box="[189,303,680,706]" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">
<heading id="D085234F6F04FFE90BFCFD68FE9FFD3E" bold="true" box="[189,303,680,706]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="122" pageNumber="123" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B90648316F04FFE90BFCFD68FE9FFD3E" bold="true" box="[189,303,680,706]" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD94236F04FFE90BFCFD17FE4EFC81" blockId="122.[189,1399,726,893]" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">
I could find no information on the collector (Moritz) and therefore cannot suggest a more precise type locality than “ 
<collectingCountry id="F365D4B36F04FFE90A1CFD39FE6AFCEF" box="[349,474,761,787]" name="Colombia" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">Colombia</collectingCountry>
”. The abdomen of the 
<typeStatus id="54C92A816F04FFE90996FD39FC8EFCEF" box="[727,830,761,787]" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">holotype</typeStatus>
is very shrivelled, but seems to have dark tergites with pale posterior margins. The very prominent frontal vitta, with a strongly convex area bearing the ocelli, is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F04FFE90AB9FC81FDC0FCA6" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Hennig" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[504,624,832,858]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="122" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oblitus">
<emphasis id="B90648316F04FFE90AB9FC81FDC0FCA6" box="[504,624,832,858]" italics="true" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">M. oblitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which has a dark thorax and different femoral banding. See also Remarks under 
<emphasis id="B90648316F04FFE90A36FCA4FE4EFC81" box="[375,510,868,893]" italics="true" pageId="122" pageNumber="123">
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F04FFE90A36FCA4FE4AFC81" authorityName="- Steyskal" authorityYear="1968" box="[375,506,868,893]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Zelatractodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="122" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scurrus">M. scurrus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
